 :tx/rationale "FIX-THRESHOLD: The model2vec join_threshold of 0.20 (embedding.rs:227) was empirically calibrated from potion-base-8M on DOGFOOD-3 observations, but the calibration was against observations, not against innate concept descriptions. Innate concepts have broad, definitional text ('Parts of the system and their boundaries — packages, modules, crates, files, services') which produces higher cosine with any software observation than observations produce with each other. The threshold should be the midpoint of the similarity distribution between observations and CONCEPTS, not between observations and observations. Empirical evidence from the dogfood: concept similarities ranged 0.34-0.74, so the threshold should be ~0.50 to achieve ~50% selectivity (top half matches, bottom half rejected). This is a one-line fix: change line 227 of embedding.rs from 0.20 to 0.50. Also update the doc comment to explain the calibration target. The HashEmbedder's inherited default of 0.65 (from the TextEmbedder trait, line 67) is closer to correct for its sparser distribution. Traces to: INV-EMBEDDING-004."
